# Dotfiles — Cursor Rules

## Safety
- Never commit or push without explicit user instruction.
- Never read or modify `machines/*/local/` — contains credentials/secrets.
- Never run destructive commands (rm -rf, force push, hard reset) without confirmation.
- Prefer targeted edits. Do not refactor or add comments beyond what was asked.

## Project Layout
- Zsh + Zim framework; config in `.zshrc`, `.zimrc`
- `~/.config` symlinks managed via `stow` (`install` script, `config/` directory)
- Machine-specific: `machines/Dales-MacBook-Pro.local/`
- Secrets (untracked): `machines/*/local/`

## Style
- Use `trash` instead of `rm` for deletions in shell scripts.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
